  </ul>

  <h2>Key Terms</h2>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>HAI:</strong> Healthcare-associated infection — infection acquired during healthcare delivery.</li>
    <li><strong>ABHR:</strong> Alcohol-based hand rub.</li>
    <li><strong>PPE:</strong> Personal protective equipment.</li>
    <li><strong>Sterile field:</strong> A microorganism-free area established around the site of an invasive procedure.</li>
    <li><strong>Strike-through contamination:</strong> Contamination of a sterile field via moisture passing through a barrier.</li>
    <li><strong>Chain of infection:</strong> Infectious agent → reservoir → portal of exit → mode of transmission → portal of entry → susceptible host.</li>
  </ul>
